What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Data Governance Market?

Market Analysis and Insights

Data Governance Market

Data governance market is expected to gain market growth in the forecast period of 2022 to 2029. Data Bridge Market Research analyses the market to reach at an estimated value of USD 34.8 billion by 2029 and grow at a CAGR of 22.30% in the above-mentioned forecast period.

Data governance is basically management of the performance of data assets and data functions. It generally deals in data integrity, security, usability, accountability and availability employed in an enterprise. The various technologies and strategies of data governance are used to make sure that business data comply with corporate policies and compliances. It is widely used in various end users such as BFSI, retail and consumer goods, government, healthcare, manufacturing, telecom and IT, energy and utilities, transportation and logistics and others.

The factors such as rising demand to ensure high data quality and heritage over the data life cycle of an enterprise and developing BI and analytics to-consumer risks are expected to emerge as the significant factors accelerating the growth of data governance market. In addition to this, various factors such as the increment in the need to wipe out client hazards, growing regulatory enforcement along with data protection issues and growing AI applications, will further aggravate the growth of the data governance market in the above-mentioned forecast period. However, the information from information silos convergence and increased risk due to lack of regulated governance along with data address validation issues results as a growth restraint for the market.

The adoption of DevOps across all company software along with increasing applications of AI in data governance is anticipated to generate lucrative opportunities for the data governance market in the forecast period of 2022 to 2029. The various complexities in maintaining security through BYOD and cloud platforms will pose as a challenge for the Data governance market.

